25#if defined(__IPHONE_12_0) || defined(__MAC_10_14)
26Sync::Sync() {}
27Sync::~Sync() {}
28
29void Sync::onDestroy()
30{
31 mMetalSharedEvent = nil;
32 mCv = nullptr;
33 mLock = nullptr;
34}
35
36angle::Result Sync::initialize(ContextMtl *contextMtl)
37{
38 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
39 {
40 mMetalSharedEvent = [[contextMtl->getMetalDevice() newSharedEvent] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
41 }
42
43 mSetCounter = mMetalSharedEvent.get().signaledValue;
44
45 mCv.reset(new std::condition_variable());
46 mLock.reset(new std::mutex());
47 return angle::Result::Continue;
48}
49
50angle::Result Sync::set(ContextMtl *contextMtl, GLenum condition, GLbitfield flags)
51{
52 if (!mMetalSharedEvent)
53 {
54 ANGLE_TRY(initialize(contextMtl));
55 }
56 ASSERT(condition == GL_SYNC_GPU_COMMANDS_COMPLETE);
57 ASSERT(flags == 0);
58
59 mSetCounter++;
60 contextMtl->queueEventSignal(mMetalSharedEvent, mSetCounter);
61 return angle::Result::Continue;
62}
63angle::Result Sync::clientWait(ContextMtl *contextMtl,
64 bool flushCommands,
65 uint64_t timeout,
66 GLenum *outResult)
67{
68 std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lg(*mLock);
69 if (mMetalSharedEvent.get().signaledValue >= mSetCounter)
70 {
71 *outResult = GL_ALREADY_SIGNALED;
72 return angle::Result::Continue;
73 }
74 if (flushCommands)
75 {
76 contextMtl->flushCommandBuffer(mtl::WaitUntilScheduled);
77 }
78
79 if (timeout == 0)
80 {
81 *outResult = GL_TIMEOUT_EXPIRED;
82
83 return angle::Result::Continue;
84 }
85
86 // Create references to mutex and condition variable since they might be released in
87 // onDestroy(), but the callback might still not be fired yet.
88 std::shared_ptr<std::condition_variable> cvRef = mCv;
89 std::shared_ptr<std::mutex> lockRef = mLock;
90#if ANGLE_MTL_EVENT_AVAILABLE
91 AutoObjCObj<MTLSharedEventListener> eventListener =
92 contextMtl->getDisplay()->getOrCreateSharedEventListener();
93 [mMetalSharedEvent.get() notifyListener:eventListener
94 atValue:mSetCounter
95 block:^(id<MTLSharedEvent> sharedEvent, uint64_t value) {
96 std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lg(*lockRef);
97 cvRef->notify_one();
98 }];
99
100 if (!mCv->wait_for(lg, std::chrono::nanoseconds(timeout),
101 [this] { return mMetalSharedEvent.get().signaledValue >= mSetCounter; }))
102 {
103 *outResult = GL_TIMEOUT_EXPIRED;
104 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
105 }
106
107 ASSERT(mMetalSharedEvent.get().signaledValue >= mSetCounter);
108 *outResult = GL_CONDITION_SATISFIED;
109#endif
110
111 return angle::Result::Continue;
112}
113void Sync::serverWait(ContextMtl *contextMtl)
114{
115 contextMtl->serverWaitEvent(mMetalSharedEvent, mSetCounter);
116}
117angle::Result Sync::getStatus(bool *signaled)
118{
119 *signaled = mMetalSharedEvent.get().signaledValue >= mSetCounter;
120 return angle::Result::Continue;
121}
122#endif // #if defined(__IPHONE_12_0) || defined(__MAC_10_14)
123} // namespace mtl

135
136angle::Result FenceNVMtl::set(const gl::Context *context, GLenum condition)
137{
138 ASSERT(condition == GL_ALL_COMPLETED_NV);
139 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
140 return mSync.set(contextMtl, GL_SYNC_GPU_COMMANDS_COMPLETE, 0);
141}
142
143angle::Result FenceNVMtl::test(const gl::Context *context, GLboolean *outFinished)
144{
145 bool signaled = false;
146 ANGLE_TRY(mSync.getStatus(&signaled));
147
148 *outFinished = signaled ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
149 return angle::Result::Continue;
150}
151
152angle::Result FenceNVMtl::finish(const gl::Context *context)
153{
154 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
155 uint64_t timeout = 1000000000ul;
156 GLenum result;
157 do
158 {
159 ANGLE_TRY(mSync.clientWait(contextMtl, true, timeout, &result));
160 } while (result == GL_TIMEOUT_EXPIRED);
161
162 if (result == GL_WAIT_FAILED)
163 {
164 UNREACHABLE();
165 return angle::Result::Stop;
166 }
167
168 return angle::Result::Continue;
169}

181angle::Result SyncMtl::set(const gl::Context *context, GLenum condition, GLbitfield flags)
182{
183 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
184 return mSync.set(contextMtl, condition, flags);
185}
186
187angle::Result SyncMtl::clientWait(const gl::Context *context,
188 GLbitfield flags,
189 GLuint64 timeout,
190 GLenum *outResult)
191{
192 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
193
194 ASSERT((flags & ~GL_SYNC_FLUSH_COMMANDS_BIT) == 0);
195
196 bool flush = (flags & GL_SYNC_FLUSH_COMMANDS_BIT) != 0;
197
198 return mSync.clientWait(contextMtl, flush, timeout, outResult);
199}
200
201angle::Result SyncMtl::serverWait(const gl::Context *context, GLbitfield flags, GLuint64 timeout)
202{
203 ASSERT(flags == 0);
204 ASSERT(timeout == GL_TIMEOUT_IGNORED);
205
206 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
207 mSync.serverWait(contextMtl);
208 return angle::Result::Continue;
209}
210
211angle::Result SyncMtl::getStatus(const gl::Context *context, GLint *outResult)
212{
213 bool signaled = false;
214 ANGLE_TRY(mSync.getStatus(&signaled));
215
216 *outResult = signaled ? GL_SIGNALED : GL_UNSIGNALED;
217 return angle::Result::Continue;
218}

232
233egl::Error EGLSyncMtl::initialize(const egl::Display *display,
234 const gl::Context *context,
235 EGLenum type)
236{
237 ASSERT(type == EGL_SYNC_FENCE_KHR);
238 ASSERT(context != nullptr);
239
240 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
241 if (IsError(mSync.set(contextMtl, GL_SYNC_GPU_COMMANDS_COMPLETE, 0)))
242 {
243 return egl::Error(EGL_BAD_ALLOC, "eglCreateSyncKHR failed to create sync object");
244 }
245
246 return egl::NoError();
247}
248
249egl::Error EGLSyncMtl::clientWait(const egl::Display *display,
250 const gl::Context *context,
251 EGLint flags,
252 EGLTime timeout,
253 EGLint *outResult)
254{
255 ASSERT((flags & ~EGL_SYNC_FLUSH_COMMANDS_BIT_KHR) == 0);
256
257 bool flush = (flags & EGL_SYNC_FLUSH_COMMANDS_BIT_KHR) != 0;
258 GLenum result;
259 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
260 if (IsError(mSync.clientWait(contextMtl, flush, static_cast<uint64_t>(timeout), &result)))
261 {
262 return egl::Error(EGL_BAD_ALLOC);
263 }
264
265 switch (result)
266 {
267 case GL_ALREADY_SIGNALED:
268 // fall through. EGL doesn't differentiate between event being already set, or set
269 // before timeout.
270 case GL_CONDITION_SATISFIED:
271 *outResult = EGL_CONDITION_SATISFIED_KHR;
272 return egl::NoError();
273
274 case GL_TIMEOUT_EXPIRED:
275 *outResult = EGL_TIMEOUT_EXPIRED_KHR;
276 return egl::NoError();
277
278 default:
279 UNREACHABLE();
280 *outResult = EGL_FALSE;
281 return egl::Error(EGL_BAD_ALLOC);
282 }
283}
284
285egl::Error EGLSyncMtl::serverWait(const egl::Display *display,
286 const gl::Context *context,
287 EGLint flags)
288{
289 // Server wait requires a valid bound context.
290 ASSERT(context);
291
292 // No flags are currently implemented.
293 ASSERT(flags == 0);
294
295 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
296 mSync.serverWait(contextMtl);
297 return egl::NoError();
298}
299
300egl::Error EGLSyncMtl::getStatus(const egl::Display *display, EGLint *outStatus)
301{
302 bool signaled = false;
303 if (IsError(mSync.getStatus(&signaled)))
304 {
305 return egl::Error(EGL_BAD_ALLOC);
306 }
307
308 *outStatus = signaled ? EGL_SIGNALED_KHR : EGL_UNSIGNALED_KHR;
309 return egl::NoError();
310}

312egl::Error EGLSyncMtl::dupNativeFenceFD(const egl::Display *display, EGLint *result) const
313{
314 UNREACHABLE();
315 return egl::EglBadDisplay();
316}
